Kennedy starts the night off talking more in depth about the Hillary Clinton Lena Dunham interview.

MICHAEL MALICE, MOLLIE HEMINGWAY, and JOANNE NOSUCHINSKY are on the panel tonight. They continue to talk about the Lena Dunham interview. Biden's popularity is growing. The way the rules are right now he could parachute in and enter the Democratic debate as late as the day before it actually airs. Senator Lindsay Graham has told the RNC to stop narrowing the 2016 Republican field.

NASA has confirmed the existence of water on Mars. DR. MICHIO KAKU is in studio to discuss.

The panel returns to talk about Just Beiber's desire to live like jesus and how going to church isn't required to do that. Quote "Going to Taco Bell doesn't make you a taco." Pumpkin Spice Latte - who cares? Nepal considers banning amateur climbing on Mount Everest. 

Kennedy does battle with a giant snake, an adorable gecko, and a sticky fingered frog. THE REPTILE GUY facilitates that. Get him back to Madagascar! gofundme.com/thereptileguy <- Be a saint, give a buck.

NIGHTCAP: Women rants onabout how Halloween is sexualizing our youth.
